Pretoria - Day five of proceedings into the #TrialOfThePlant saw a flurry of green, yellow, red and black colours outside the Gauteng High Court, Pretoria as pro-cannabis supporters finally made their voices heard. The supporters held up placards with the messages in support of legalisation and some went as far as taping their mouths shut with industrial tape. “Healing myself should not be a crime. If nature is illegal, freedom doesn’t exist; and Cannabis: no hangover, no violence, no regrets,” were slogans placed across their placards. The supporters handed out their own pamphlets. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
